	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-07-14T04:32:53">Oxus Gold Plc (Oxus) is a United Kingdom-based company engaged in the investment in Amantaytau Goldfields (AGF) in Uzbekistan. The Company operates in two segments: Metal and Corporate. The Metals segment, comprising precious and base metals operations at different stages, from field exploration through to mine development and precious metals production. The Metals segment includes the Company's principal mining, development and exploration activities in Uzbekistan through its interest in AGF. The Corporate segment includes the corporate cost center primarily serving administrative and fund raising functions to support the Metals segment. It operates in the United Kingdom and Malta in support of its operations in Uzbekistan. It holds two projects, which include AGF and Khandiza mining assets in Uzbekistan. Its wholly owned subsidiaries include Oxus Holdings (Malta) Limited and Marakand Minerals Limited.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2015-10-18T21:43:24">BRIEF: For the six months ended 30 June 2015, Oxus Gold plc revenues was not reported. Net loss decreased 21% to $1.1M. Lower net loss reflects Arbitration expenses decrease of 64% to $153K (expense), Administrative expenses decrease of 6% to $530K (expense).</Text>
	</TextInfo>
